What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

template <typename T, typename U>
auto multiply(T a, U b)
{
    return a * b;
}

int main()
{
    std::cout << multiply(4, 3) << '\n';
    std::cout << multiply(4, 0.5) << '\n';
    std::cout << multiply(3.0, 2) << '\n';
    return 0;
}
```

This template is supposed to print `ratio: 2.5` but it prints `ratio: 2`. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

template <typename T>
T divide(T a, T b)
{
    return a / b;
}

int main()
{
    std::cout << "ratio: " << divide(5, 2) << '\n';
    return 0;
}
```
